        "text_GVrHCD": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>We believe there are some biomechanics to how the skeleton and skull work, which result in it collapsing over time.</p><p>Particularly if you did orthodontics, extractions, or grind your teeth our experience is that this could result in the skull sort of 'deflating'.</p><p>And a simple mouthguard like Reviv can 'reinflate' it by stretching the soft tissue that covers the skull.</p>"
