    "collapsible_content_rnYPMG": {
      "type": "collapsible-content",
      "blocks": {
        "collapsible_row_knCQ7X": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How should I start Reviv?  Is there anything to be aware of?",
            "icon": "check_mark",
            "row_content": "<p>Yes there are a few things to know going in.</p><p><strong>On wearing it:</strong> The standard pattern is overnight + 2-3 hours during the day. Build up gradually with shorter intervals during the day first rather than going straight to overnights — that helps the soft tissue adjust. Most folks find the early phase is the hardest part and it gets significantly easier after a few weeks usually.</p><p><strong>On early discomfort:</strong> Pretty common in the first few weeks. Sore teeth, achy gums, occasional small sores in the mouth, the lips not closing fully, extra saliva — all signs the soft tissue is stretching, not signs something is wrong. Take it at your own pace. If the soreness gets sharp, take a short break — a few hours or even a day or two off is fine. Stick with it but don't push through pain.</p><p><strong>On accelerating results:</strong> What matters most is consistent use and then stretching to accelerate. The Fast Method in our Skool community has some stretches we recommend, including the Bite & Hold exercise that works alongside the mouthguard: <a href=\"https://www.skool.com/reviv-2885/classroom/8ca49f79?md=90728adac0e5463680dc40a43e294104\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.skool.com/reviv-2885/classroom/8ca49f79?md=90728adac0e5463680dc40a43e294104</a></p><p><strong>On mouth taping:</strong> A lot of folks tape at night to keep the mouth closed and help with guard retention while the tissue is still adjusting. Pairs well with the Reviv.</p><p><br/>A good place to learn more before and during the process is our Skool community — 1 month free trial: <a href=\"https://www.skool.com/reviv-2885/about\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.skool.com/reviv-2885/about</a></p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_7bqjan": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Why does this work?",
            "icon": "lightning_bolt",
            "row_content": "<p>Think of the soft tissue (e.g., fascia & skin) covering the bones of the skull as a balloon. When you grind your teeth down, it is as if you're taking air out of the balloon.</p><p>When this balloon deflates, it crushes the skull, which in turn crushes the brain and causes cognitive and neurological issues over time.</p><p>In general, we as a society like to call this process 'aging.' But if you grind down your teeth faster, you 'age' faster. The good part is you can reverse the process by using the same physics in reverse, i.e., you 'add' height back to the teeth.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_dQ9kQP": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How many people have done this process?",
            "icon": "check_mark",
            "row_content": "<p>Over 20,000 people have started using the appliance and this method since late 2024.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_jBBByU": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How does sizing work?",
            "icon": "lightning_bolt",
            "row_content": "<p>Note that there is a 'Size Chart' above that you should refer to for measurements of our appliances.<strong><br/></strong>We generally recommend adults to get a large as our large is not that large and our small is pretty small.</p><p>- The small can be used for children from about age 8 and up.<br/>- Most adults with a smaller mouth will be fine with a small or a large, but will generally get a bit more of a stretch with our large.<br/>- We have a special offer to get both sizes for the same price when purchasing the support package.  So write to cs@getreviv.com if you want instructions on how to do that.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_AWRC8x": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "What is support?",
            "icon": "lightning_bolt",
